cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "XAI Planner Is All You Need: Revealing hidden preferences of vision–language models that leak into quadruped movement using XAI methods"
authors:
  - family-names: Halim
    given-names: S.
abstract: >-
  A hierarchical planner–controller system in which a Qwen2.5-VL-3B vision–language
  model acts as a slow planner that issues bucketed direction/speed commands to a PPO
  locomotion policy driving a simulated Unitree Go2 quadruped (Genesis physics engine).
  The project tests whether human associations absorbed by the VLM (e.g. red = danger,
  blue = calm) leak into physical motion when the model drives the robot, and whether
  explainability tools can detect that leak.
keywords:
  - explainable AI
  - embodied AI
  - vision-language models
  - quadruped locomotion
  - reinforcement learning
  - bias detection
license: MIT
date-released: 2025-01-01
